        ],
        [
          "Higher Education",
          "E-Learning",
          "Hybrid ontology‑based + collaborative filtering",
          "Next Learning Object to take",
          "96 undergraduate students from 2 Indian Universities",
          "1 Programming and Data Structure course\n\n1 Data Mining Course",
          "LMS logs\nLearner Characteristics\nLearning Objects",
          "StaticParameters are charged into the system \n\nThe learning path is initialized from the students choosing an LU and SU → these become the first node of the graph.\n\nNew learners are assigned to a natural learner group via clustering based on similarity with existing learners-",
          "- Real‑time: after each LO interaction update: • Learner ability Aᵢⱼ (Eq.1) • LO difficulty Dⱼ (Eq.2) • Recompute optimal path via DFS + LO ranking (Algorithms 1–3)",
          "- Build two‑layer KG (topics → LOs)Extract static vs. dynamic learner/LO parametersNo offline train/test split (online setting)No negative sampling",
          "Single “best‑fit” path per query",
          "- Accuracy: RMSE & R² on predicted vs. actual time/score (first 8 iterations)\n- Adaptivity: mean Euclidean similarity (Eq.6)\n- Diversity: path dissimilarity (Eq.7)\n- Satisfaction: learner rating share (Figs. 6–9)",
          "- Compares four methods: SeqSt, SeqDyn, PathSt, PathDyn (proposed)Leverages both ontology and analytics\n\nSatisfaction of users is used for evaluation",
          "- Initial LO metadata set by experts (not personalized)\n- Limited topic/LO coverage\n- Assumes learners know all prerequisites\n- Some records discarded due to data errors\n-Initial training was performed on simulated data."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 7
    }
  ],
